The paper deals with managing uncertainty in the Semantic Web, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves combining description logics with probability theory, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of Prolog for implementing the tableau algorithm suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB), as Prolog is often used for querying databases. The paper also discusses the performance of DL reasoners, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR), as efficient reasoning is important in both fields.
